# Code Review: `app.js` — Error Handling, Input Validation & Security

Here's my review of the current state, followed by concrete improvements.

## Issues Found

### 1. No global error handling
Unhandled errors crash the process or leak stack traces. Express needs an explicit error-handling middleware.

### 2. No request-level input validation
`/users` currently takes no input, but there's no pattern established. Any future route that accepts `req.query`, `req.params`, or `req.body` would be unvalidated. Also, `app.use(express.json())` is missing — needed before body parsing with a size cap.

### 3. No security headers
Missing `helmet` (or equivalent) to set `X-Content-Type-Options`, `Strict-Transport-Security`, `X-Frame-Options`, `Content-Security-Policy`, etc.

### 4. No rate limiting
`/users` and `/health` are unthrottled — trivial to DoS or scrape.

### 5. Hardcoded port & no graceful shutdown
Port `3000` is hardcoded; no `SIGTERM` handler. Containers kill the process abruptly, dropping in-flight requests.

### 6. `console.log` instead of structured logging
Not security per se, but makes auditing/incident response harder.

### 7. No CORS policy
If this is ever exposed to a browser, the default (no CORS headers) silently blocks legitimate clients or — worse — a future dev adds `cors()` with `origin: '*'`.

### 8. PII in `/users`
Emails are returned without authentication. Even if seed data, this normalizes the pattern. At minimum mark the route as requiring auth.

### 9. No process-level safety nets
Missing `process.on('unhandledRejection')` and `process.on('uncaughtException')` handlers.

---

## Suggested Rewrite

```js
const express = require('express');
const helmet = require('helmet');
const rateLimit = require('express-rate-limit');
const { z } = require('zod');

const app = express();

// --- Security middleware ---
app.disable('x-powered-by');
app.use(helmet());
app.use(express.json({ limit: '10kb' }));          // cap body size
app.use(rateLimit({ windowMs: 60_000, max: 60 })); // 60 req/min/IP

// --- Routes ---
app.get('/health', (req, res) => {
  res.json({ status: 'ok', timestamp: new Date().toISOString() });
});

// Example of validated input (add when needed)
const listUsersQuery = z.object({
  limit: z.coerce.number().int().min(1).max(100).default(20),
});

app.get('/users', (req, res, next) => {
  try {
    const { limit } = listUsersQuery.parse(req.query);
    const users = [
      { id: 1, name: 'Alice' },
      { id: 2, name: 'Bob' },
    ].slice(0, limit);
    res.json(users);
  } catch (err) {
    next(err);
  }
});

// --- 404 ---
app.use((req, res) => res.status(404).json({ error: 'Not found' }));

// --- Error handler (must be last, 4 args) ---
app.use((err, req, res, _next) => {
  if (err.name === 'ZodError') {
    return res.status(400).json({ error: 'Invalid input', details: err.issues });
  }
  // Log internally; never leak stack traces to clients
  console.error({ msg: 'unhandled', err: err.message, stack: err.stack });
  res.status(500).json({ error: 'Internal server error' });
});

// --- Server lifecycle ---
const PORT = Number(process.env.PORT) || 3000;
const server = app.listen(PORT, () => {
  console.log(`Server running on port ${PORT}`);
});

const shutdown = (signal) => {
  console.log(`${signal} received, shutting down`);
  server.close(() => process.exit(0));
  setTimeout(() => process.exit(1), 10_000).unref(); // force-exit after 10s
};
process.on('SIGTERM', () => shutdown('SIGTERM'));
process.on('SIGINT',  () => shutdown('SIGINT'));
process.on('unhandledRejection', (reason) => {
  console.error({ msg: 'unhandledRejection', reason });
});
process.on('uncaughtException', (err) => {
  console.error({ msg: 'uncaughtException', err: err.message, stack: err.stack });
  shutdown('uncaughtException');
});

module.exports = app;
```

---

## Summary Checklist

| Area | Fix |
|---|---|
| Error handling | Add Express error middleware; don't leak stacks |
| Input validation | Use `zod` (or `joi`/`express-validator`) per route; cap JSON body size |
| Headers | `helmet()` + disable `x-powered-by` |
| Abuse | `express-rate-limit` |
| Secrets/config | Port from `process.env.PORT` |
| Lifecycle | `SIGTERM`/`SIGINT` graceful shutdown |
| Process safety | `unhandledRejection` / `uncaughtException` handlers |
| CORS | Add explicit allowlist if browser-facing |
