  const id = Number.parseInt(req.params.id, 10);
  if (!Number.isInteger(id) || id <= 0) {
    return res.status(400).json({ error: 'Invalid id' });
  }
  // ...
});
```
Never interpolate `req.params`/`req.query`/`req.body` into SQL, shell, file paths, or `RegExp` without validation or parameterization.

### 6. Don't leak internals from `/health` — line 8
`timestamp` is fine, but avoid exposing version numbers, hostnames, or DB status to unauthenticated callers. Keep `/health` minimal; put richer diagnostics behind auth on `/internal/health`.

