`/users` returns email addresses unauthenticated. Even for seed data, treat PII as a first-class concern: gate the endpoint behind auth and return only fields the caller is authorized to see. Consider a serializer layer so you can't accidentally leak fields added to the model later.

## 5. Configuration hardcoding

